    <item>
      <title>Running Windows on a Chromebook</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/en/posts/windows-on-chromebook/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2024 19:05:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/posts/windows-on-chromebook/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A guide to installing windows on a Lenove 100e gen2 ast chromebook (for archive purposes)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-you-need&#34;&gt;What you need&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A Lenovo 100e/300e gen2 ast Chromebook.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A sd card or usb drive.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A mouse (wired, or dongle only).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Power adapter for the chromebook.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Ventoy downloaded for your OS&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Drivers downloaded from this guide.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Tiny11 iso downloaded from this guide.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;downloads&#34;&gt;Downloads&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.mediafire.com/file/vn0ucvdb389sxl3/tiny11_23H2_x64.iso/file&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Tiny 11 ISO&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ventoy.net&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Ventoy&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://aka.ms/vs/17/release/vc_redist.x64.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Visual C++ Redist&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/coolstar/driverinstallers/raw/master/cr50/cr50.1.0.1-installer.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;CR50 TPM Driver&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/coolstar/driverinstallers/raw/master/crosec/crosec.2.0.6-installer.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Chrome EC Driver&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amd.com/en/resources/support-articles/release-notes/RN-RAD-WIN-21-5-2.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Radeon GPU Drivers&lt;/a&gt;&#xA; &lt;strong&gt;!!DO NOT INSTALL UNTIL READING THE GUIDE!!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://coolstar.org/chromebook/downloads/drivers/stoney-amdkmdag-patch.zip&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Radeon GPU Driver Patch&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/coolstar/driverinstallers/raw/master/crostouchpad/crostouchpad.4.1.6-installer.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Touchpad Drivers&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/coolstar/driverinstallers/raw/master/crostouchscreen/crostouchscreen.2.9.5-installer.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Touchscreen Drivers&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/coolstar/driverinstallers/raw/master/csaudioacp2x/csaudioacp2x.1.0.0-installer.exe&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Audio Drivers&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.7-zip.org/download.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;7Zip&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://win32subsystem.live/supermium/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Supermium&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;getting-started&#34;&gt;Getting Started&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;an-overview&#34;&gt;An Overview&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This guide will show you how to go from chromeOS to Windows 11, you will need an internet connection for the chromebook, and also the other requirements listed &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/#downloads&#34;&gt;above&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
